    label: 'Wounded in a raid',
    pool: 'biographical',
    isMajor: false,
    flavour: {
      male:   'He took a wound that should have been worse and was bad enough. The wound came from the man who gave it to him — who did not survive to discuss it. He healed badly, as most things healed on the heath, and carries the record of it in the way that warriors carry records — not displayed, not mentioned, but available for inspection by anyone who knows how to read a man\'s body for its history.',
    },
