      male:   'He swallowed the boar root. The augur watched him do it with the expression of someone observing a process that was going to resolve one way or another and had no preference regarding which. Three men had died in the last ceremony. He survived. What he experienced during the surviving is not something he has the language for, in Pagaelin or in anything else. He is Raunir now. One who touched the Walker\'s cloak. The other warriors look at him differently. He is not certain whether this is respect or distance.',
      female: 'She survived the tasparth. The augur named her Raunir in the ceremony of recognition, using the liturgical tongue, which she did not then understand. She understood later, when she was taught. Raunir: one who touched the Walker\'s cloak. What she touched during the ordeal was not a cloak. She has not corrected the terminology. She has filed the discrepancy away.',
