      male:   'The shaman read the signs before the hunt — the raven\'s flight, the direction of the wind, the specific quality of the morning\'s silence. He told them where Saraen\'s hand was pointing. He was right, which he was most of the time. The hunt was good. He brought his portion back and gave the first cut to the shaman as the rite required. He has done this forty times. He does not think about it as ritual. He thinks about it as the thing that works.',
      female: 'The shaman performed the rite and she watched from the permitted distance. She has the old knowledge in pieces — her grandmother had given her fragments before she died. She knows which part of the bird\'s behaviour is relevant and which is weather. She has not told the shaman what she knows. She is not certain why.',
