  // ── PAGAELIN UNKILLED WARRIOR — ESCALATING RISK EVENTS ───────────────────
  // The pre-kill period is the most dangerous time in a Pagaelin man's life.
  // These events represent the escalating desperation of men who have not yet
  // killed — each attempt increases the chance of both success and death.
  //
  // The social reality: an unkilled man has no status, no women, no household.
  // He is a body attached to someone else's war party. The dominant men use him
  // for the dangerous work precisely because his death costs them nothing.
