    label: 'Refused a dishonourable order',
    pool: 'biographical',
    isMajor: true,
    flavour: {
      male:   'His lord had given an order he could not follow. Not would not — could not, in the sense that following it would have made him someone he did not want to be and could not have looked at in still water. He refused, formally, with witnesses. He was not punished. That surprised him more than the order had.',
      female: 'The order was to burn the village. The people were Morgathian sympathisers, the officer said, which may even have been true. She refused in front of the column and said Larani\'s name when she did it. There was a silence. The officer did not repeat the order. She has never understood why.',
    },
