      male:   'He made a vow at the chapel before the campaign: if he returned, he would give a year\'s service in Larani\'s name. He returned. He spent considerable time afterward determining what a year\'s service meant and whether he was fulfilling it adequately.',
      female: 'The vow was made in private, to the sword-altar, in language she had not planned and could not quite reproduce afterward. She survived. She has been paying the debt ever since in ways she has not always been able to name — small acts, a certain quality of attention, a refusal of one particular easy choice, repeated.',
