      male:   'He made an oath in the dark, in the ditch, bleeding. He does not remember the exact words. He remembers the sense of them clearly — what he was offering, what he was asking for. He survived. He has been paying the debt in small ways ever since, without ever being certain the accounting is correct.',
      female: 'The vow she made at the temple gate before the assault was specific and she has never told anyone what it was. She has kept it. She will keep it. She is not certain Larani heard it. She is not certain she needs Larani to have heard it for it to be binding.',
