      male:   'The chapter meeting takes three hours for forty minutes of actual business. He has learned to bring something to do during the debates about precedent. He has also learned which debates to stay awake for, since some of them, if you miss the moment, will still be running ten years later.',
      female: 'She attends every chapter meeting. She is usually the only woman and she has found that this confers an accidental advantage: when she speaks, the room goes quiet in a way it does not always for the others, whether from respect or from the novelty she cannot always tell, but she uses it consistently.',
