    label: 'Entered noble patronage as resident harper',
    pool: 'biographical',
    isMajor: true,
    flavour: {
      male:   'The lord\'s factor had heard him play at a merchant\'s dinner and sent a letter. The terms were generous: room, board, a private chamber, access to the library, and a fee that was more than his last three years of public performance combined. In exchange he played at table three evenings a week and instructed the lord\'s children. He found, to his mild surprise, that he preferred the arrangement to freedom.',
      female: 'The lady had heard of her and sent for her directly, which was unusual — most nobles went through the college. The invitation was for a month\'s trial, which became three years. She gave lessons, performed on important occasions, and had more time for her own composition than she had ever had in a free position. The arrangement ended when the lord died. She still visits the household at Highsummer.',
    },
