    pool: 'biographical',
    isMajor: true,
    flavour: {
      male:   'Two years underground made him a freeman. The guild gave him a tin medallion as legal proof, which he wore for a decade before it was stolen and which he has spent twenty years wishing he still had. His former lord sent someone to contest the freedom in the first year. The mine moot ruled for him. He did not return to his home village. He has not been back in thirty years and thinks about it occasionally.',
      female: 'The guild\'s charter was clear: two years of employment made any serf legally free. She had known this before she left. She had planned for two years, not one day more, and had taken the journeyman\'s examination in her nineteenth month so the result would be ready when her time was up. The tin medallion she received is the only document she has ever owned. She keeps it.',
    },
