      male:   'He lay in the grass above the trail and counted the guards. Six armed men, two of them good. The cargo was covered with oiled cloth, which meant it was worth protecting from weather, which meant it was worth taking. The dominant man decided the guards were too many and moved them on. He watched the caravan pass below and thought about the gap between what he could see and what he knew. The gap was mostly the two good guards.',
      female: 'She counted the people in the caravan and sorted them: merchants, drivers, guards, the woman in the second wagon who was probably a merchant\'s wife or a factor\'s daughter and who looked out at the grass as if she knew she was being watched. She was being watched. They held the look across sixty feet of open distance for a moment before the wagon moved on. She thought about what that woman\'s life looked like from inside it.',
