      female: 'She carried the water. She scraped the hides. She tended the fire at the worst hours. She did this because she was the youngest and most recently acquired and this is what the youngest wife does — she is the bottom of the household hierarchy until someone younger arrives. She is watching the older wives with the attention of someone who intends to understand the position they hold and what it costs to hold it. She has been watching for two seasons. She knows more about the camp\'s internal politics than any of the men do, none of whom are paying attention to any of it.',
