    pool: 'biographical',
    isMajor: true,
    minGapYears: 20,
    flavour: {
      male:   'The first patron of any real standing. Not the introductory contracts the house arranges for all new practitioners — those are structured, supervised, low-risk. This is the first time he has managed a significant patron relationship entirely on his own terms, with his own reading of what the man wants and needs and what the contract should include. He got two out of three things right on the first meeting. He was honest with himself about which one he got wrong and corrected it at the second meeting. The patron renewed.',
      female: 'She had been told what to expect. The reality was more complicated than the description, which is true of most things, and not in the way that makes the complication unmanageable — in the way that makes it interesting. She learned more about how merchant houses think about succession in three months with this patron than she had learned from any other source. She also learned something about herself that she had not known, which she is keeping private for now.',
    },
