      male:   'The guild trains its members in things that other guilds do not train: music at a functional level, the kind of conversation that makes someone feel heard, the specific arts of the Halean tradition that are not merely physical but include the management of attention and atmosphere. The trainers are experienced members who have retired to instructional roles. He is good at some of this and less good at other parts. He is better at the listening than the music. He is trying to determine whether the music can be developed or whether his limit is real and permanent.',
      female: 'The music instruction is twice a week and the conversation arts are every day, embedded in every interaction. The housekeeper is a former senior member and teaches by example rather than explanation — you watch her manage a difficult patron and then you have been shown something that no amount of direct instruction would have communicated. She watches. She is beginning to understand what she is watching.',
