      male:   'The senior member dealt with the lord who had been drinking since the second hour after noon with a specific combination of warmth, misdirection, and managed escalation that produced the outcome: the lord left in a good mood without the evening becoming anything that would require the guild\'s involvement or the house mistress\'s attention. He watched the whole sequence. He could identify perhaps half the techniques being deployed. He is working on identifying the other half.',
      female: 'The patron was volatile. The senior member managed him over four hours so smoothly that the patron would not have been able to identify, afterward, the specific moments when the situation had been steered. She watched it from a position that allowed observation without interference. She has been thinking about it for two weeks. She is becoming better at naming the techniques. She is not yet close to being able to deploy them at that level. She is aware that the gap between naming and deploying is most of the work.',
