      female: 'She memorised the Tormau lineage and then discovered that three of the records she had used contained an error introduced forty years ago by a previous herald who had confused two cousins with the same given name. She corrected the records and reported the correction to the guild. The guild officer thanked her. She has since developed the habit of cross-checking every genealogy she learns against at least two independent sources. It adds time to the memorisation. She considers it non-negotiable.',
