      male:   'The delivery took him through the glassblowers\' quarter and he watched for an hour before he realised he was late. What struck him was not the skill — he understood skilled work — but the specific kind of problem-solving: the way the blower was working against the material\'s tendency, not with it. His trade works with the material\'s tendency. The two approaches produced different relationships between the craftsman and the thing being made. He has been thinking about which produces better work.',
      female: 'She was sent to collect a pattern from the leatherworkers\' guild house and waited while the guild officer found the document. She watched the cutting floor from the window. The leatherworkers had a different relationship with waste than her own trade — they cut for maximum material conservation, which produced a different kind of thinking about the pattern itself. She came back with the document and three observations she has been applying to her own practice.',
