      male:   'He was the junior herald at the investiture, which meant he carried the rolls and held the register and did not speak. He watched the senior heralds work: the precision of the ceremonial language, the way each element of the ceremony was structured to produce a legal and social fact that would stand for decades. A knighting is not just a ritual — it is a document produced in bodies and words that the law recognises. He understood this abstractly before. He understands it now as something he witnessed.',
