      female: 'She took her loom to her mother\'s house and worked from there for a year. The guild does not certify home-weavers; this is an area where the guild\'s coverage is incomplete by design, because the women who weave at home are not the women the guild is designed to serve. She is not sure whether this is convenient or an insult. She sold everything she produced and used the money to buy better materials. Then she went back to the guild workshop.',
